Files containing the handler implementation for App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostCommentController@store:

- app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostCommentController.php

Explanation:
- The routes/api.php imports App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostCommentController and registers the nested route posts.comments with the store method.
- The implementation of the store method for this controller is located in app/Http/Controllers/Api/V1/PostCommentController.php.
- This file defines the PostCommentController class (within the Api\V1 namespace) and includes the store method that creates a new comment for the specified post using the authenticated user, validates via CommentsRequest, and returns a CommentResource. It also broadcasts a CommentPosted event.

Note:
- There is another PostCommentController at app/Http/Controllers/PostCommentController.php (non-API/web context), but it does not implement App\Http\Controllers\Api\V1\PostCommentController@store. The relevant API handler is in the Api/V1 path listed above.
